race.comment: BELTA OF A SONG (2) resumed further improved when beaten a nose at Belmont with Pike aboard. She tackled stronger than this at Ascot following, and was safely held beaten 2.5L. This suits better and Pike is reunited, She's likely to settle back and can finish over the top.  SHOWLAS (1) is a leader busting to win. Conceded late this grade/trip at Ascot last time and has a 3kg claimer aboard today. That brings her right into it and drawn handy she'll get every chance. CAPE LEEUWIN (3) is third-up and should be ready to show more like his best. Before the spell he led and was just nudged out in a Belmont Open 3 over this distance, and he has an inside barrier today and a handy 2kg claim. UNIVERSAL HOTNESS (7) is third-up off a narrow defeat here in a CL5. This looks a bit tougher, but he races forward and won't be far away.
